29/06/2004
ISTANBUL, Turkey -- Defence Minister Vecdi Gonul met with his Greek counterpart, Spilios Spiliotopoulos, for an hour Monday (28 June) on the sidelines of the NATO summit in Istanbul.
They discussed mutual reductions in weapons programmes and efforts to stabilise Southeast Europe.
They also decided to step up direct communication between their ministries.
Gonul also attended a meeting with his counterparts from Macedonia, the United States and Iraq.
Macedonia's Vlado Buckovski assured them that Skopje is ready to join the international community and participate in the training of the Iraqi Army.
(MPA, A1 TV - 28/06/04)
